🎯 Aim
To create and use a Slicer in Power BI to interactively filter and analyze sales data based on Region.
________________________________________
🧩 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Power BI Desktop.
2.	Click Home → Get Data → Excel.
3.	Select the file PowerBI_Slicer_Practice.xlsx and click Load.
4.	After loading, go to the Report View.
5.	Insert a Bar Chart from the Visualizations pane.
6.	Drag the Product field to the Axis area.
7.	Drag the Sales field to the Values area.
8.	Click on a blank space in the report canvas.
9.	Select the Slicer visual from the Visualizations pane.
10.	Drag the Region field into the Slicer.
11.	Click different region values (North, South, East, West) and observe the changes in the bar chart.


